                      Standards                      

Modes

Each calculator has to contain 2 modes, which is 
determined base on arguments

- Argument mode: Specifies the expression in
  arguments, used when detected there are arguments in 
  `argv`.
- Interactive mode: Expressions are entered after
  program started, or piped to `stdin` of the program. 
  Used when no arguments are added

Tokenization
                                                     
All calculators should support both the expression
being seperated via spaces like `1 + 1 / 2` or the
expression combined like `1+1/2`, which leads to the
need of tokenization when expressions are in combined
mode.

